To evaluate \( T = \sum_{k=0}^{2026} (-1)^k \binom{2026}{k} / (k+2) \), recognize that \( 1/(k+2) = \int_0^1 x^{k+1} \, dx \). Thus,

\[
T = \sum_{k=0}^{2026} (-1)^k \binom{2026}{k} \int_0^1 x^{k+1} \, dx = \int_0^1 x \sum_{k=0}^{2026} \binom{2026}{k} (-x)^k \, dx = \int_0^1 x (1 - x)^{2026} \, dx.
\]

This is the beta function: \( \int_0^1 x^{2-1} (1-x)^{2027-1} \, dx = B(2, 2027) = \frac{\Gamma(2) \Gamma(2027)}{\Gamma(2029)} = \frac{1! \cdot 2026!}{2028!} = \frac{2026!}{2028 \times 2027 \times 2026!} = \frac{1}{2027 \times 2028} \).

The fraction \( \frac{1}{2027 \times 2028} \) is reduced, as 2027 and 2028 are coprime.

\[
\boxed{
\begin{matrix}
\frac{ \\ 1 \\ }{ \\ 2027 \\ \times \\ 2028 \\ } \end{matrix}
}
\]
